JOHANNESBURG &#8211; South Africa&#8217;s rand gained in early trade on Monday on improved appetite for riskier assets while stock futures pointed to a slightly lower open on the main bourse.At 0650 GMT, the rand traded at 12.7600 per dollar, 0.43% stronger than its Friday close.Last week&#8217;s low of 12.79/$ offers support.Fitch and S&amp;P kept South Africa&#8217;s sovereign rating unchanged last week. Moody&#8217;s decision is expected on Friday.Stocks were set to open lower at 0700 GMT, with the JSE securities exchange&#8217;s Top-40 futures index down 0.22%.In fixed income, the yield for the benchmark government bond due in 2026 was 2 basis points lower to 8.43%.